Package grafioschtrader.reportviews.securitydividends

Class AccountDividendPosition

java.lang.Object
grafioschtrader.reportviews.securitydividends.AccountDividendPosition
Direct Known Subclasses:
CashAccountPosition, SecurityDividendsPosition
public abstract class AccountDividendPosition extends Object
Abstract base class for managing dividend and interest position calculations within an account. This class provides common functionality for tracking dividend payments, interest income, tax withholdings, and position valuations across different currencies.

The class handles currency conversions to the main currency (MC) and maintains precision settings for different currencies. It tracks both taxable and tax-free income, automatic tax withholdings, and end-of-year position valuations.

    • updatedTaxes

      protected void updatedTaxes(Transaction transaction, double exchangeRate)
      Updates the tax-related calculations based on a transaction. This method processes dividend/interest transactions and updates the following:
      • Real received dividend/interest amount in main currency
      • Automatically paid tax amounts (both position and main currency)
      • Taxable amounts for interest transactions or taxable interest
      • Tax-free income for non-taxable dividend transactions
      Parameters:
      transaction - the transaction to process for tax calculations
      exchangeRate - the exchange rate to convert from position currency to main currency

    • getAndSetExchangeRateEndOfYear

      protected void getAndSetExchangeRateEndOfYear(Map<Integer,Historyquote> historyquoteIdMap, DateTransactionCurrencypairMap dateCurrencyMap, String currencySearched)
      Retrieves and sets the exchange rate at the end of the year for the specified currency. This method looks up the appropriate currency pair and historical quote to determine the exchange rate that should be used for end-of-year valuations.

      If the searched currency is the same as the main currency, no exchange rate is needed. Otherwise, the method attempts to find the currency pair and corresponding historical quote to set both the closing price and exchange rate for year-end calculations.

      Parameters:
      historyquoteIdMap - map of security currency IDs to their historical quotes
      dateCurrencyMap - map containing currency pair information and main currency
      currencySearched - the currency code for which to find the exchange rate
